      <h4><%= link_to "Foreign Affairs", foreign_path %> Rejection of Detente - December 24th 1979</h4>
      <p>"Detente" often refers to the easing of tension between the United States and the Soviet Union.  This tension was created during the Cold War, and the two powers have been working to lower the tension.  However, the Detente ended after the Soviet Intervention in Afghanistan.</p>
      <hr>
      <h4><%= link_to "Criminal Activity", criminal_path %> Death of John Lennon - December 8th 1980</h4>
      <p>John Lennon was a famous musician and was one of the founders of the Beatles.  He gained fame not only from the Beatles, but also his solo career, and his political activism and pacifism.  He was shot by Mark David Chapman at the entrance of the building he lived in, and was pronounced Dead On Arrival at the Roosevelt Hospital.</p>
