      <p>The Loomis Fargo Bank Robbery was a $17.3 million robbery in Charlotte, North Carolina.  The heist was put on by the armored car driver and vault Supervisor David Scott Ghantt.  The federal investigation resulted in the arrest of 8 people directly involved in the heist, aswell as 16 people indirectly involved.  </p>
